97781.name: Earnings of tertiary-educated workers relative to workers with upper-secondary education (OECD (2017))
97781.description:
Earnings advantage of tertiary-educated workers relative to workers with upper-secondary education. Estimates correspond to workers ages 25-64. Regular earnings data collection provides information based on an annual, monthly or weekly reference period,
depending on the country. The length of the reference period for earnings also differs. Data on earnings are before income tax.
97781.datasetName: Relative earnings of adults, by educational attainment - Education at a Glance 2017: OECD Indicators (2017)
97781.s_name: Education at a Glance 2017: OECD Indicators (2017)

source.name: Education at a Glance 2017: OECD Indicators (2017)
source.additionalInfo: The year of reference is 2015 for all countries except: Denmark (2014), Finland (2014), Belgium (2014), Italy (2013), Canada (2014), Netherlands (2014), Japan (2012), Spain (2014), France (2013), Luxembourg (2014), Poland (2014), and Lithuania (2014). Earnings are net of income tax for: Latvia, Ireland, and Mexico. Index 100 refers to the combined ISCED levels 3 and 4 of the educational attainment levels in the ISCED 2011 classification for: Switzerland, Luxembourg, Turkey, Czech Republic, Slovakia, the United States, Colombia, and Brazil. For further details, see Table A6.1 in the Education at a Glance 2017 report.
